## IT2 — Figma MCP landscape + Code Mode integration

### Official Figma MCP (remote vs desktop): endpoints, transport, auth, tool surface

Remote server:

- Endpoint: `https://mcp.figma.com/mcp`.
- Transport: HTTP MCP. Figma’s Claude Code example is `claude mcp add --transport http figma https://mcp.figma.com/mcp`; VS Code config uses `"type": "http"` and `"url": "https://mcp.figma.com/mcp"`. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/
- Auth: Figma OAuth. The remote setup requires signing in through Figma’s OAuth flow. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/
- Feature scope: Figma says the remote server is recommended, does not require the desktop app, and has the broadest feature set. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/
- Client gate: Figma says only clients listed in the Figma MCP Catalog can connect; unsupported clients must join a waitlist. This is the main Code Mode risk. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/
- Access/rate limits: View/Collab seats get up to 6 calls/month. Full/Dev seats get higher limits: Starter and Professional up to 200/day with 10/min or 15/min, Organization up to 200/day with 15/min, Enterprise up to 600/day with 20/min. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/rate-limits-access/
- Write access: `use_figma` write-to-canvas requires a Full seat; Dev seats can use read-only workflows like design context, variables, and screenshots. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/write-to-canvas/

Desktop/local server:

- Endpoint: `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp`.
- Transport: HTTP MCP. Figma’s Claude Code example is `claude mcp add --transport http figma-desktop http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp`. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/
- Auth/session: runs through the logged-in Figma desktop app; setup requires latest Figma desktop app, an open Figma Design file, Dev Mode enabled, and “Enable desktop MCP server” in the MCP server section. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/
- Feature scope: Figma positions desktop as for specific organization/enterprise needs and says remote is preferred/broadest. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/
- Selection support: desktop supports current-selection prompting; remote is link-based and requires a frame/layer link. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/ and https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/

Official tool surface from Figma docs:

- Shared/non-remote-only tools: `add_code_connect_map`, `get_code_connect_map`, `get_code_connect_suggestions`, `get_design_context`, `get_figjam`, `get_metadata`, `get_screenshot`, `get_variable_defs`, `send_code_connect_mappings`.
- Remote-only tools: `create_new_file`, `generate_diagram`, `generate_figma_design`, `get_context_for_code_connect`, `get_libraries`, `search_design_system`, `upload_assets`, `use_figma`, `whoami`.
- Correction to known facts: current official docs list `get_design_context`, not `get_code`; and `get_screenshot`, not `get_image`. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/

Better optional Code-Mode default:

- Default to official remote MCP when Code Mode can authenticate/connect, because it is Figma’s recommended path, has no desktop-app dependency, and exposes the broadest tool surface. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/
- Keep desktop as the practical fallback for Code Mode if remote OAuth/catalog gating fails, or when the desired workflow is “current Figma desktop selection → design context/variables/screenshots.” Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/

### Community alternatives + verdict

Notable alternatives:

- Framelink / GLips `figma-developer-mcp`: mature third-party stdio MCP that uses a Figma personal access token, simplifies Figma API responses for coding agents, and is already present in this repo’s `.utcp_config.json` as manual `figma` using `npx -y figma-developer-mcp@latest --stdio` with `FIGMA_API_KEY`. Sources: `.utcp_config.json:69-88`, https://github.com/GLips/Figma-Context-MCP, https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-developer-mcp
- `grab/cursor-talk-to-figma-mcp`: plugin/WebSocket-based bridge between an MCP server and a Figma plugin. It supports reading and modifying designs, but has heavier setup: Bun, WebSocket server, Figma plugin, channel join. Source: https://github.com/grab/cursor-talk-to-figma-mcp
- Fetch failure: `https://github.com/FramelinkAI/figma-developer-mcp` returned 404; the package/repo source is `GLips/Figma-Context-MCP`.

Pros/cons:

- Official MCP pros: supported by Figma, OAuth, broad remote-only tools, Code Connect integration, write-to-canvas path. Sources: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/ and https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/code-connect-integration/
- Official MCP cons: catalog/client gating, OAuth flow uncertainty inside Code Mode, plan/seat rate limits. Sources: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/ and https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/rate-limits-access/
- Framelink pros: stdio, token-based, simple Code Mode fit, already modeled in local config, popular package with active npm distribution. Sources: `.utcp_config.json:69-88`, https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-developer-mcp
- Framelink cons: third-party, read/design-context focused, not the official Figma MCP feature surface.
- TalkToFigma pros: rich programmatic modification surface through a plugin bridge. Source: https://github.com/grab/cursor-talk-to-figma-mcp
- TalkToFigma cons: too much operational setup for an optional secondary path in `mcp-figma`.

Verdict: support official-first, plus document Framelink as the compatibility fallback because it already fits this project’s Code Mode stdio pattern. Do not support TalkToFigma in this skill unless the skill explicitly expands into Figma plugin automation.

### Code Mode registration (.utcp_config.json entry — concrete paste-ready example)

This project’s real Code Mode config uses `manual_call_templates[]`, each with `name`, `call_template_type: "mcp"`, and nested `config.mcpServers`. Chrome DevTools is registered as stdio under matching manual/server names like `chrome_devtools_1`, and tools are later called as `chrome_devtools_1.chrome_devtools_1_{tool}`. Sources: `.utcp_config.json:14-31`, `.opencode/skills/mcp-chrome-devtools/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:134-154`

Code Mode HTTP support: the local Code Mode server imports `@utcp/mcp` and `@utcp/http`, and its package depends on `@utcp/mcp`. Sources: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/mcp_server/index.ts:17-20`, `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/mcp_server/package.json:58-67`. The `@utcp/mcp` package documents MCP transport support for both `stdio` and `http`, with `transport: "http"` and `url`. Source: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@utcp/mcp

Paste-ready remote official entry:

```json
{
  "name": "figma",
  "call_template_type": "mcp",
  "config": {
    "mcpServers": {
      "figma": {
        "transport": "http",
        "url": "https://mcp.figma.com/mcp",
        "timeout": 60,
        "sse_read_timeout": 300
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Paste-ready desktop fallback entry:

```json
{
  "name": "figma_desktop",
  "call_template_type": "mcp",
  "config": {
    "mcpServers": {
      "figma_desktop": {
        "transport": "http",
        "url": "http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp",
        "timeout": 60,
        "sse_read_timeout": 300
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Compatibility fallback if direct HTTP OAuth does not work in Code Mode:

```json
{
  "name": "figma",
  "call_template_type": "mcp",
  "config": {
    "mcpServers": {
      "figma": {
        "transport": "stdio",
        "command": "npx",
        "args": [
          "-y",
          "mcp-remote@latest",
          "https://mcp.figma.com/mcp",
          "--transport",
          "http-first"
        ],
        "env": {}
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Rationale: `mcp-remote` bridges stdio-only clients to remote MCP servers with auth support and can try HTTP first. Source: https://www.npmjs.com/package/mcp-remote

### Code Mode invocation (call_tool_chain example)

Code Mode naming rule in this project: call tools as `{manual_name}.{manual_name}_{tool_name}`. Sources: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md:214-220`, `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/references/naming_convention.md:20-37`

Discovery first:

```ts
const tools = await search_tools({
  task_description: "Figma design context variables screenshot metadata",
  limit: 20
});

const designContextInfo = await tool_info({
  tool_name: "figma.figma_get_design_context"
});

const variableInfo = await tool_info({
  tool_name: "figma.figma_get_variable_defs"
});
```

Desktop current-selection example:

```ts
const result = await call_tool_chain({
  code: `
    console.log("Reading Figma current selection via desktop MCP...");

    const [designContext, variables, metadata] = await Promise.all([
      figma_desktop.figma_desktop_get_design_context({}),
      figma_desktop.figma_desktop_get_variable_defs({}),
      figma_desktop.figma_desktop_get_metadata({})
    ]);

    return {
      success: true,
      source: "figma_desktop",
      designContext,
      variables,
      metadata
    };
  `
});
```

Remote link/node example:

```ts
const result = await call_tool_chain({
  code: `
    const figmaUrl = "https://www.figma.com/design/FILE_KEY/Name?node-id=NODE_ID";

    console.log("Reading Figma remote design context...");

    const [designContext, variables, metadata, codeConnect] = await Promise.all([
      figma.figma_get_design_context({ url: figmaUrl }),
      figma.figma_get_variable_defs({ url: figmaUrl }),
      figma.figma_get_metadata({ url: figmaUrl }),
      figma.figma_get_code_connect_map({ url: figmaUrl })
    ]);

    return {
      success: true,
      source: "figma_remote",
      designContext,
      variables,
      metadata,
      codeConnect
    };
  `
});
```

Parameter caveat: Figma’s public docs describe link-based and selection-based behavior but do not expose JSON schemas for each MCP tool on the docs pages fetched. Run `tool_info()` after registration and adapt `url`, `nodeId`, or file-key parameters to the discovered schema before treating the snippet as final. Sources: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/, `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md:246-252`

Cleanup:

- Static `.utcp_config.json` registrations do not need per-call cleanup.
- If using dynamic `register_manual`, use `deregister_manual({ manual_name: "figma" })` after experimentation. Code Mode exposes `register_manual` and `deregister_manual`. Source: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/mcp_server/index.ts:165-180`

### CLI-vs-MCP routing line for mcp-figma

Use `figma-cli` as primary for direct, fast, scriptable Figma operations: inspect/export/create/modify assets or files through a terminal-first workflow.

Use optional Figma MCP via Code Mode when the agent needs design context from Figma as model input: design context, variables/styles, metadata, screenshots, Code Connect mappings, design-system search, or remote write-to-canvas workflows.

Analog to Chrome skill: CLI is the fast/token-efficient/default path; MCP is the type-safe multi-tool orchestration path. Source for Chrome routing pattern: `.opencode/skills/mcp-chrome-devtools/SKILL.md:194-253`

### Gotchas & constraints

- Remote Figma MCP is recommended and broadest, but only catalog-listed clients can connect; Code Mode/OpenCode may hit this gate. Sources: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/ and https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/
- Remote auth is OAuth, not a Figma API token. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/remote-server-installation/
- Desktop server requires Figma desktop, latest app, an open Design file, Dev Mode, and enabling the desktop MCP server. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/
- Desktop endpoint is fixed at `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp`; port conflicts or disabled desktop server will make Code Mode discovery fail. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/local-server-installation/
- Selection-based prompting only works with desktop; remote requires a link to a frame/layer. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/
- Rate limits and access depend on plan and seat; View/Collab seats are severely limited. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/rate-limits-access/
- Write-to-canvas requires Full seat and has limitations: 20kb output response limit per call, no assets/image support yet for that tool, custom fonts unsupported, beta quality. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/write-to-canvas/
- MCP responses can be token-heavy; prefer `get_metadata` before `get_design_context` for large designs because Figma documents `get_metadata` as a sparse XML outline for drilling down. Source: https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/tools-and-prompts/
- Code Mode’s local docs still show older stdio/SSE examples and the existing repo config currently registers third-party Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`, not official Figma MCP. Sources: `.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/references/configuration.md:253-283`, `.utcp_config.json:69-88`

